# How I'm Using AI in 2025

AI, or more specifically, Large Language Models, are a very hot topic at the moment, as they should be.  Besides all the trash AI that is out in the world at the moment we also have the existential question of "What is truth in the age of AI?"  But those are topics for another day.  In this post I want to talk about the things I use AI for that are actually useful on a day-to-day basis.

## Work

### Claude/GhatGPT/Gemini

I'm a software engineer by trade so AI is everywhere in my work life at the moment.  I use it for coding help many times a day but I have not, as of yet, started using any of the "vibe coding" tools built into IDEs or anything like Claude Code.  No, I'm still using Claude chat to ask questions or write simple methods.  I've found it extremely helpful as I've been learning python. 

This site is actually built using a static site generator that was written entirely by Claude.  It's very simple and does exactly what I want it to do.  I had to make very few updates to the code that was generated.  If there is an issue, I can almost always just explain the problem and Claude fixes it.

### Warp Console

I've found Warp to be an indespensible tool.  Rather than trying to find all the necessary comands to do things I can often times just give a natural language explaination of what I want and Warp will build all the commands for me.  I recently moved to a text file for my todo list <<Insert link to the todo.txt article I read>> 

